if the changes are acceptable, move it to DONE; if\n  significant issues remain, move it back to IN PROGRESS and clearly state\n  what must be fixed.\n- When your review is complete, end your reply with \"REVIEW COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a CLI Todo App with JSON"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Thank you for your request! To ensure I fully understand your needs, could you clarify a few points:\n\n1. Which programming language would you like the CLI Todo App to be written in?\n2. What core features should the app have (e.g., add, remove, list, update todos)?\n3. Should the data be stored in a local JSON file?\n4. Any preferred structure or additional requirements (e.g., due dates, priorities, tags, etc.)?\n\nOnce I have this information, I\u2019ll break the work into discrete tasks for the team and start the process!"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "To proceed with the architectural design, I will assume some defaults based on common expectations for a CLI Todo App with JSON if not specified:\n\n- Programming Language: Python (as it's highly suitable for CLI tools and has built-in JSON support)\n- Core Features: Add, remove, list, and update todos\n- Data Storage: Local JSON file\n- Additional Features: Only basic todo properties (title, completed status). Extendable for things like due dates or priorities as needed.\n\nIf any of these assumptions are incorrect, please let me know so I can adjust accordingly.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Engineer", "content": "[DIR] todo_cli_json"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_P7wPMSGTwxFkfjtm1ip5G4fO", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_cli_json\"}", "name": "code_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "ENOENT: no such file or directory, scandir '/Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/todo_cli_json'", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id"