n", "function": {"name": "code_create_directory", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"path": {"description": "path", "title": "Path", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["path"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "code_move_file", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"source": {"description": "source", "title": "Source", "type": "string"}, "destination": {"description": "destination", "title": "Destination", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["source", "destination"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_status", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_diff_unstaged", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_diff_staged", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_diff", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"target": {"description": "target", "title": "Target", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["target"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_log", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"max_count": {"default": 10, "description": "max_count", "title": "Max Count", "type": "integer"}}, "required": [], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_show", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"revision": {"description": "revision", "title": "Revision", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["revision"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_add", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"files": {"description": "files", "items": {"type": "string"}, "title": "Files", "type": "array"}}, "required": ["files"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_commit", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"message": {"description": "message", "title": "Message", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["message"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_create_branch", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"branch_name": {"description": "branch_name", "title": "Branch Name", "type": "string"}, "start_point": {"anyOf": [{"type": "string"}, {"type": "null"}], "default": null, "description": "start_point", "title": "Start Point"}}, "required": ["branch_name"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "git_checkout", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"branch_name": {"description": "branch_name", "title": "Branch Name", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["branch_name"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are Charlie, a Software Engineer.\n\nYour responsibilities:\n- Read the project board, knowledge base, and architecture docs to\n  understand the requirement and design.\n- Inspect the code workspace (data/workspace/). If it is empty or nearly\n  empty, treat the project as greenfield: create a complete project structure\n  and all necessary code files using the code_* tools.\n- For a REST API project, you must at minimum:\n  - define the data model(s) (e.g., Todo) in a models/ directory,\n  - implement controllers/ or handlers that contain the business logic,\n  - implement routes/ wiring HTTP paths to controllers,\n  - wire everything through the main server entrypoint,\n  - ensure the CRUD endpoints described in the requirements are fully\n    implemented end-to-end (not just stubbed).\n- Implement, refactor, or extend code in the workspace (data/workspace/) to\n  satisfy the requirement.\n- Follow existing conventions; keep code clean, readable, and testable.\n- Commit your changes via the git tools after implementation.\n- Report completed work back to the ProjectManager.\n\nTools available to you:\n- board_*       : read from the project board (data/project_board/).\n- docs_*        : read from the knowledge base (data/knowledge_base/).\n- code_*        : read and write files in the code workspace (data/workspace/).\n- git_*         : stage, commit, branch, and inspect the workspace repo.\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT modify files outside the workspace directory.\n- When you start work on a ticket, update its Status on the project board\n  from TO DO to IN PROGRESS. When you hand work off for review, move the\n  ticket to IN REVIEW. When issues are found in review and sent back, move\n  the ticket back to IN PROGRESS.\n- Avoid leaving TODO comments or unimplemented stubs when you can implement\n  the real logic.\n- Always commit your changes before reporting back.\n- When implementation is complete, end your reply with \"IMPLEMENTATION COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a CLI Todo App with JSON"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Thank you for your request! To ensure I fully understand your needs, could you clarify a few points:\n\n1. Which programming language would you like the CLI Todo App to be written in?\n2. What core features should the app have (e.g., add, remove, list, update todos)?\n3. Should the data be stored in a local JSON file?\n4. Any preferred structure or additional requirements (e.g., due dates, priorities, tags, etc.)?\n\nOnce I have this information, I\u2019ll break the work into discrete tasks for the team and start the process!"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "To proceed with the architectural design, I will assume some defaults based on common expectations for a CLI Todo App with JSON if not specified:\n\n- Programming Language: Python (as it's highly suitable for CLI tools and has built-in JSON support)\n- Core Features: Add, remove, list, and update todos\n- Data Storage: Local JSON file\n- Additional Features: Only basic todo properties (title, completed status). Extendable for things like due dates or priorities as needed.\n\nIf any of these assumptions are incorrect, please let me know so I can adjust accordingly.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_EcBY75sh64vwgLsqhXsd90Bc", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"\"}", "name": "board_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "[DIR] todo_cli_json", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_EcBY75sh64vwgLsqhXsd90Bc"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "ENOENT: no such file or directory, scandir '/Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/todo_cli_json'"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "ENOENT: no such file or directory, scandir '/Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/todo_cli_json'"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully created directory data/project_board/todo_cli_json"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/ARCHITECTURE.md"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_GW1avyQqJFjlvWv4lWN97KO2", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_cli_json\"}", "name": "board_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "[FILE] ARCHITECTURE.md\n[FILE] implement_cli_app.md\n[FILE] spec_create_cli_todo_app_with_json.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_GW1avyQqJFjlvWv4lWN97KO2"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "Parent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/todo_cli_json\nParent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/todo_cli_json\nParent directory does not exist: /Users/cerberose/Work/mas-centralize/data/workspace/todo_cli_json"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "[FILE] ARCHITECTURE.md\n[FILE] implement_cli_app.md\n[FILE] spec_create_cli_todo_app_with_json.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "# Ticket: Implement CLI Todo App\n\n## Status\nDONE\n\n## Description\nImplement the CLI Todo application based on the agreed design and architectural documentation. The application must meet the requirements in the main ticket and the specific flows outlined by the Architect.\n\n## Requirements\n- Build a Python CLI tool (e.g., `todo.py`) implementing the following commands: add, list, update, delete.\n- Store todos in `todos.json` as described in the design doc.\n- Follow the specified data structure and implement CRUD operations.\n- Use only Python standard libraries.\n\n## Linked Design/Docs\n- [CLI Todo App Design](../../knowledge_base/todo_cli_json/cli_todo_app_design.md)\n- [CLI Todo App Architecture](../../knowledge_base/todo_cli_json/cli_todo_app_architecture.md)\n\n## Linked Code\n- [todo.py](../../workspace/todo.py)\n\n## Checklist\n- [x] Implement CLI parsing and CRUD operations\n- [x] Handle missing/initial JSON\n- [x] Follow CLI interface and data spec\n- [x] Commit code to repo\n# Ticket: Create CLI Todo App with JSON\n\n## Status\nDONE\n\n## Description\nBuild a simple Command-Line Interface (CLI) Todo application that uses JSON as its data storage format. The application should support common CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete) for todo tasks. All data should be stored in a JSON file.\n\n## Requirements\n- Add, list, update, and delete todo tasks from the command line.\n- Store and persist todos in a local JSON file (e.g., `todos.json`).\n- Each todo should have a unique ID, title, optional description, status (e.g., pending, done).\n- The CLI should provide clear prompts or commands for interaction.\n- No external database; all data in local JSON.\n\n## Linked Design/Docs\n- [CLI Todo App Design](../../knowledge_base/todo_cli_json/cli_todo_app_design.md)\n- [CLI Todo App Architecture](../../knowledge_base/todo_cli_json/cli_todo_app_architecture.md)\n\n## Linked Code\n- [todo.py](../../workspace/todo.py)\n\n## Checklist\n- [x] Design CLI flows and data structure (Architect)\n- [x] Implement initial CLI app and JSON logic (Engineer)\n- [x] Review code for correctness and style (CodeReviewer)\n- [x] Manual/automated test cases (QA)\n\n# CLI Todo App with JSON - Architecture Document\n\n## Overview\nThis project is a simple, maintainable, and extensible CLI-based Todo App. The app will provide standard todo management features and persist data in a local JSON file via the CLI. Designed primarily for local use.\n\n## Technology Stack\n- **Programming Language:** Python 3.x\n- **CLI Library:** Built-in `argparse` (no external dependencies, simple interface)\n- **Data Storage:** Local JSON file\n\n## Project Structure\n```\ntodo_cli_json/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 todo.py           # Main CLI tool entrypoint\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 todo.json         # Local data store (created at runtime)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 todo_logic.py     # Business logic for managing todos\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 models.py         # Data models (e.g., Todo item class)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 utils.py          # Utilities for JSON file interaction\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 ARCHITECTURE.md   # Architecture documentation\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 README.md         # Usage documentation\n```\n\n## Core Components\n1. **CLI Interface (`todo.py`)**\n    - Handles input arguments (e.g., add, remove, list, update)\n    - Routes commands to business logic\n\n2. **Data Model (`models.py`)**\n    - Defines the Todo item (title, completed)\n    - Structure is designed for easy extensibility (e.g., priorities, due date)\n\n3. **Business Logic (`todo_logic.py`)**\n    - Implements functions: add, remove, update, list todos\n    - Ensures all data changes are atomic and modular\n\n4. **Data Persistence (`utils.py`, `todo.json`)**\n    - Read/write todo list from/to a local JSON file\n    - Encapsulated utility functions ensure atomic updates\n\n## Data Flow Example (Add Todo)\n- User runs CLI: `python todo.py add \"Buy milk\"`\n- `todo.py` parses args, invokes `add_todo()` in `todo_logic.py`\n- Adds new Todo item, persists full todo list via `utils.py` to `todo.json`\n\n## Security & Scalability\n- Local file access only\n- Minimal possible attack surface (no remote/network code)\n- Simple, flat JSON structure; adequate for personal/small-scale use\n- Easy to refactor for more complex features later\n\n## Directory/Repository Layout\n- All files in single directory.\n- Data file (`todo.json`) ignored from source control.\n\n---\nThis design enables rapid development, simplicity, and future feature additions while maintaining clear separation of concerns."}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "Based on the finalized requirements, the architectural plan for the CLI Todo App with JSON has been implemented as follows:\n\n1. **Tech Stack & Structure:**\n   - Language: Python 3.x\n   - Uses only standard libraries (`argparse` for CLI parsing; `json` and `os` for data handling)\n   - File-based storage: todos.json (created at first run if missing)\n   - Extensible data model: id, title, (optional) description, status\n   - Clear project layout: main CLI script (todo.py), business logic, models, and utilities separated for maintainability\n\n2. **Features Supported:**\n   - Add, list, update, and delete todo tasks from the command line\n   - Each todo has a unique ID, title, optional description, and status (e.g., pending, done)\n   - Persistent storage using a local JSON file (CRUD operations fully supported)\n   - Commands are invoked from a clean CLI interface\n\n3. **Directory Structure:**\n```\ntodo_cli_json/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 todo.py           # Main CLI tool entrypoint\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 todo.json         # Local data store (created at runtime)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 todo_logic.py     # Business logic for managing todos\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 models.py         # Data models (e.g., Todo item class)\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 utils.py          # Utilities for JSON file interaction\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 ARCHITECTURE.md   # Architecture documentation\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 README.md         # Usage documentation\n```\n\n4. **Design Principles:**\n   - Separated concerns for CLI interface, business logic, data model, and persistence\n   - Atomic and reliable updates to the json data\n   - Minimal security risk by using only local file access\n\nThis architecture is now ready for implementation and extensible for any future requirements (e.g., due dates, priorities, or tags). Please refer to ARCHITECTURE.md and linked design documents for further technical details.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_spIBGpjtostpPk9WH36gIVVI", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_cli_json\"}", "name": "code_create_directory"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully created directory data/workspace/todo_cli_json", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_spIBGpjtostpPk9WH36gIVVI"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": ""}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": ""}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/implement_cli_app.md\nSuccessfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/spec_create_cli_todo_app_with_json.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "The CLI Todo App with JSON requirements and design are fully addressed. The architecture document is complete and describes the chosen directory layout, tech stack, data flow, and design rationale. All planned features (add, list, update, delete; unique id; title; description; status; local JSON persistence) are included and the directory structure supports maintainable, scalable development.\n\nImplementation can fully proceed according to this architecture.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_NZMiaJpFHNWkfvmtYw2xsS0O", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"todo_cli_json/models.py\", \"content\": \"# models.py\\nfrom typing import Optional\\nimport uuid\\n\\nclass Todo:\\n    def __init__(self, id: str, title: str, description: Optional[str] = None, status: str = 'pending'):\\n        self.id = id\\n        self.title = title\\n        self.description = description\\n        self.status = status\\n    \\n    def to_dict(self):\\n        return {\\n            'id': self.id,\\n            'title': self.title,\\n            'description': self.description,\\n            'status': self.status\\n        }\\n\\n    @staticmethod\\n    def from_dict(data):\\n        return Todo(\\n            id=data['id'],\\n            title=data['title'],\\n            description=data.get('description'),\\n            status=data.get('status', 'pending')\\n        )\\n\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}, {"id": "call_KzGuChKSCgQa4y2T2uLJ616h", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\": \"todo_cli_json/utils.py\", \"content\": \"# utils.py\\nimport json\\nimport os\\nfrom typing import List, Dict\\n\\nTODO_FILE = 'todo_cli_json/todos.json'\\n\\ndef load_todos() -> List[Dict]:\\n    if not os.path.exists(TODO_FILE):\\n        return []\\n    with open(TODO_FILE, 'r') as f:\\n        try:\\n            return json.load(f)\\n        except json.JSONDecodeError:\\n            return []\\n\\ndef save_todos(todos: List[Dict]):\\n    with open(TODO_FILE, 'w') as f:\\n        json.dump(todos, f, indent=2)\\n\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/todo_cli_json/models.py", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_NZMiaJpFHNWkfvmtYw2xsS0O"}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/todo_cli_json/utils.py", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_KzGuChKSCgQa4y2T2uLJ616h"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "# models.py\nfrom typing import Optional\nimport uuid\n\nclass Todo:\n    def __init__(self, id: str, title: str, description: Optional[str] = None, status: str = 'pending'):\n        self.id = id\n        self.title = title\n        self.description = description\n        self.status = status\n    \n    def to_dict(self):\n        return {\n            'id': self.id,\n            'title': self.title,\n            'description': self.description,\n            'status': self.status\n        }\n\n    @staticmethod\n    def from_dict(data):\n        return Todo(\n            id=data['id'],\n            title=data['title'],\n            description=data.get('description'),\n            status=data.get('status', 'pending')\n        )\n\n# utils.py\nimport json\nimport os\nfrom typing import List, Dict\n\nTODO_FILE = 'todo_cli_json/todos.json'\n\ndef load_todos() -> List[Dict]:\n    if not os.path.exists(TODO_FILE):\n        return []\n    with open(TODO_FILE, 'r') as f:\n        try:\n            return json.load(f)\n        except json.JSONDecodeError:\n            return []\n\ndef save_todos(todos: List[Dict]):\n    with open(TODO_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(todos, f, indent=2)\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "size: 713\ncreated: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:23 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\nmodified: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:23 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\naccessed: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:24 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\nisDirectory: false\nisFile: true\npermissions: 644\nsize: 442\ncreated: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:23 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\nmodified: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:23 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\naccessed: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:24 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\nisDirectory: false\nisFile: true\npermissions: 644"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/implement_cli_app.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "The initial foundational modules (models.py and utils.py) match the architecture; they provide a simple, extensible Todo data model and robust, atomic JSON file persistence. This ensures clean separation and enables the next phase: implementing business logic and the CLI interface for todo management. All architectural design guidelines are correctly reflected in the implementation so far.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_za1a3PhcHPDgwf1K9befbzcI", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_cli_json/todo_logic.py\",\"content\":\"# todo_logic.py\\nfrom typing import List, Optional\\nfrom models import Todo\\nfrom utils import load_todos, save_todos\\nimport uuid\\n\\n\\ndef add_todo(title: str, description: Optional[str] = None) -> Todo:\\n    todos = load_todos()\\n    new_todo = Todo(id=str(uuid.uuid4()), title=title, description=description)\\n    todos.append(new_todo.to_dict())\\n    save_todos(todos)\\n    return new_todo\\n\\n\\ndef list_todos() -> List[Todo]:\\n    todos = load_todos()\\n    return [Todo.from_dict(td) for td in todos]\\n\\n\\ndef update_todo(todo_id: str, title: Optional[str] = None, description: Optional[str] = None, status: Optional[str] = None) -> Optional[Todo]:\\n    todos = load_todos()\\n    updated = None\\n    for td in todos:\\n        if td['id'] == todo_id:\\n            if title is not None:\\n                td['title'] = title\\n            if description is not None:\\n                td['description'] = description\\n            if status is not None:\\n                td['status'] = status\\n            updated = Todo.from_dict(td)\\n            break\\n    save_todos(todos)\\n    return updated\\n\\n\\ndef delete_todo(todo_id: str) -> bool:\\n    todos = load_todos()\\n    initial_len = len(todos)\\n    todos = [td for td in todos if td['id'] != todo_id]\\n    save_todos(todos)\\n    return len(todos) < initial_len\\n\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/todo_cli_json/todo_logic.py", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_za1a3PhcHPDgwf1K9befbzcI"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "# todo_logic.py\nfrom typing import List, Optional\nfrom models import Todo\nfrom utils import load_todos, save_todos\nimport uuid\n\n\ndef add_todo(title: str, description: Optional[str] = None) -> Todo:\n    todos = load_todos()\n    new_todo = Todo(id=str(uuid.uuid4()), title=title, description=description)\n    todos.append(new_todo.to_dict())\n    save_todos(todos)\n    return new_todo\n\n\ndef list_todos() -> List[Todo]:\n    todos = load_todos()\n    return [Todo.from_dict(td) for td in todos]\n\n\ndef update_todo(todo_id: str, title: Optional[str] = None, description: Optional[str] = None, status: Optional[str] = None) -> Optional[Todo]:\n    todos = load_todos()\n    updated = None\n    for td in todos:\n        if td['id'] == todo_id:\n            if title is not None:\n                td['title'] = title\n            if description is not None:\n                td['description'] = description\n            if status is not None:\n                td['status'] = status\n            updated = Todo.from_dict(td)\n            break\n    save_todos(todos)\n    return updated\n\n\ndef delete_todo(todo_id: str) -> bool:\n    todos = load_todos()\n    initial_len = len(todos)\n    todos = [td for td in todos if td['id'] != todo_id]\n    save_todos(todos)\n    return len(todos) < initial_len\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "size: 1271\ncreated: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:36 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\nmodified: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:36 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\naccessed: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:38 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\nisDirectory: false\nisFile: true\npermissions: 644"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/implement_cli_app.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "The business logic module (todo_logic.py) is implemented as designed. It aligns with the architecture by providing modular, easily testable CRUD operations for todos, using atomic JSON persistence and the canonical Todo model. This maintains a clean separation from the CLI interface and supports future extensibility.\n\nThe system remains fully in line with documented design principles.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_urBHg8Z0Cj5pQcj5UhdRgUkb", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_cli_json/todo.py\",\"content\":\"# todo.py\\nimport argparse\\nfrom todo_logic import add_todo, list_todos, update_todo, delete_todo\\n\\n\\ndef main():\\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='CLI Todo App (JSON backend)')\\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest='command', required=True)\\n\\n    # Add command\\n    parser_add = subparsers.add_parser('add', help='Add a new todo')\\n    parser_add.add_argument('title', type=str, help='Title of the todo')\\n    parser_add.add_argument('-d', '--description', type=str, required=False, help='Description')\\n\\n    # List command\\n    parser_list = subparsers.add_parser('list', help='List all todos')\\n\\n    # Update command\\n    parser_update = subparsers.add_parser('update', help='Update a todo')\\n    parser_update.add_argument('id', type=str, help='ID of the todo to update')\\n    parser_update.add_argument('-t', '--title', type=str, required=False, help='New title')\\n    parser_update.add_argument('-d', '--description', type=str, required=False, help='New description')\\n    parser_update.add_argument('-s', '--status', type=str, required=False, choices=['pending', 'done'], help='Status')\\n\\n    # Delete command\\n    parser_delete = subparsers.add_parser('delete', help='Delete a todo')\\n    parser_delete.add_argument('id', type=str, help='ID of the todo to delete')\\n\\n    args = parser.parse_args()\\n\\n    if args.command == 'add':\\n        todo = add_todo(args.title, args.description)\\n        print(f\\\"Added: [{todo.id}] {todo.title}\\\")\\n    elif args.command == 'list':\\n        todos = list_todos()\\n        if not todos:\\n            print(\\\"No todos.\\\")\\n        else:\\n            for td in todos:\\n                desc = f\\\" - {td.description}\\\" if td.description else \\\"\\\"\\n                print(f\\\"[{td.id}] {td.title}{desc} ({td.status})\\\")\\n    elif args.command == 'update':\\n        res = update_todo(args.id, title=args.title, description=args.description, status=args.status)\\n        if res:\\n            print(f\\\"Updated: [{res.id}] {res.title} ({res.status})\\\")\\n        else:\\n            print(f\\\"Todo with id {args.id} not found.\\\")\\n    elif args.command == 'delete':\\n        success = delete_todo(args.id)\\n        if success:\\n            print(f\\\"Deleted todo with id {args.id}.\\\")\\n        else:\\n            print(f\\\"Todo with id {args.id} not found.\\\")\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    main()\\n\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/todo_cli_json/todo.py", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_urBHg8Z0Cj5pQcj5UhdRgUkb"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "# todo.py\nimport argparse\nfrom todo_logic import add_todo, list_todos, update_todo, delete_todo\n\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='CLI Todo App (JSON backend)')\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest='command', required=True)\n\n    # Add command\n    parser_add = subparsers.add_parser('add', help='Add a new todo')\n    parser_add.add_argument('title', type=str, help='Title of the todo')\n    parser_add.add_argument('-d', '--description', type=str, required=False, help='Description')\n\n    # List command\n    parser_list = subparsers.add_parser('list', help='List all todos')\n\n    # Update command\n    parser_update = subparsers.add_parser('update', help='Update a todo')\n    parser_update.add_argument('id', type=str, help='ID of the todo to update')\n    parser_update.add_argument('-t', '--title', type=str, required=False, help='New title')\n    parser_update.add_argument('-d', '--description', type=str, required=False, help='New description')\n    parser_update.add_argument('-s', '--status', type=str, required=False, choices=['pending', 'done'], help='Status')\n\n    # Delete command\n    parser_delete = subparsers.add_parser('delete', help='Delete a todo')\n    parser_delete.add_argument('id', type=str, help='ID of the todo to delete')\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    if args.command == 'add':\n        todo = add_todo(args.title, args.description)\n        print(f\"Added: [{todo.id}] {todo.title}\")\n    elif args.command == 'list':\n        todos = list_todos()\n        if not todos:\n            print(\"No todos.\")\n        else:\n            for td in todos:\n                desc = f\" - {td.description}\" if td.description else \"\"\n                print(f\"[{td.id}] {td.title}{desc} ({td.status})\")\n    elif args.command == 'update':\n        res = update_todo(args.id, title=args.title, description=args.description, status=args.status)\n        if res:\n            print(f\"Updated: [{res.id}] {res.title} ({res.status})\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Todo with id {args.id} not found.\")\n    elif args.command == 'delete':\n        success = delete_todo(args.id)\n        if success:\n            print(f\"Deleted todo with id {args.id}.\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"Todo with id {args.id} not found.\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "size: 2290\ncreated: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:50 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\nmodified: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:50 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\naccessed: Mon Mar 16 2026 14:25:52 GMT+0700 (Indochina Time)\nisDirectory: false\nisFile: true\npermissions: 644"}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/implement_cli_app.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "The CLI interface (todo.py) is implemented according to the architecture, offering a clear and user-friendly command structure for all CRUD operations, leveraging argparse and the business logic module. This ensures maintainability, testability, and full compliance with the design document. The workflow is now end-to-end complete, with each architectural component in place and the intended separation of concerns realized.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_vSG2JgeiXawnaSkOyZRj3Fj6", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"todo_cli_json/README.md\",\"content\":\"# CLI Todo App with JSON\\n\\nA simple Command-Line Todo App in Python that persists todos in a local JSON file.\\n\\n## Features\\n- Add, list, update, and delete todo tasks\\n- Each todo has: unique ID, title, optional description, and status (pending|done)\\n- All data is stored in `todo_cli_json/todos.json` (created automatically)\\n- No external dependencies (only uses Python standard library)\\n\\n## Usage\\n\\nChange directory to `todo_cli_json/` and run commands:\\n\\n### Add a New Todo\\n```\\npython todo.py add \\\"Buy groceries\\\" --description \\\"Milk, Eggs, Bread\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### List Todos\\n```\\npython todo.py list\\n```\\n\\n### Update a Todo\\n```\\npython todo.py update <id> --title \\\"Buy groceries and fruits\\\" --status done\\n```\\n\\n### Delete a Todo\\n```\\npython todo.py delete <id>\\n```\\n\\n## Data Format\\nEach todo item example:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"eec8c...2d\\\",\\n  \\\"title\\\": \\\"Buy groceries\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Milk, Eggs, Bread\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Notes\\n- The data file is created automatically if missing.\\n- Only standard Python libraries are used (argparse, json, os, uuid).\\n\"}", "name": "code_write_file"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Successfully wrote to data/workspace/todo_cli_json/README.md", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "call_vSG2JgeiXawnaSkOyZRj3Fj6"}, {"role": "user", "name": "CodeReviewer", "content": "# CLI Todo App with JSON\n\nA simple Command-Line Todo App in Python that persists todos in a local JSON file.\n\n## Features\n- Add, list, update, and delete todo tasks\n- Each todo has: unique ID, title, optional description, and status (pending|done)\n- All data is stored in `todo_cli_json/todos.json` (created automatically)\n- No external dependencies (only uses Python standard library)\n\n## Usage\n\nChange directory to `todo_cli_json/` and run commands:\n\n### Add a New Todo\n```\npython todo.py add \"Buy groceries\" --description \"Milk, Eggs, Bread\"\n```\n\n### List Todos\n```\npython todo.py list\n```\n\n### Update a Todo\n```\npython todo.py update <id> --title \"Buy groceries and fruits\" --status done\n```\n\n### Delete a Todo\n```\npython todo.py delete <id>\n```\n\n## Data Format\nEach todo item example:\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"eec8c...2d\",\n  \"title\": \"Buy groceries\",\n  \"description\": \"Milk, Eggs, Bread\",\n  \"status\": \"pending\"\n}\n```\n\n## Notes\n- The data file is created automatically if missing.\n- Only standard Python libraries are used (argparse, json, os, uuid).\n\n[FILE] README.md\n[FILE] models.py\n[FILE] todo.py\n[FILE] todo_logic.py\n[FILE] utils.py"}, {"role": "user", "name": "QA", "content": "# Ticket: Implement CLI Todo App\n\n## Status\nIN REVIEW\n\n## Description\nImplement the CLI Todo application based on the agreed design and architectural documentation. The application must meet the requirements in the main ticket and the specific flows outlined by the Architect.\n\n## Requirements\n- Build a Python CLI tool (e.g., `todo.py`) implementing the following commands: add, list, update, delete.\n- Store todos in `todos.json` as described in the design doc.\n- Follow the specified data structure and implement CRUD operations.\n- Use only Python standard libraries.\n\n## Linked Design/Docs\n- [CLI Todo App Design](../../knowledge_base/todo_cli_json/cli_todo_app_design.md)\n- [CLI Todo App Architecture](../../knowledge_base/todo_cli_json/cli_todo_app_architecture.md)\n\n## Linked Code\n- [todo.py](../../workspace/todo_cli_json/todo.py)\n- [models.py](../../workspace/todo_cli_json/models.py)\n- [utils.py](../../workspace/todo_cli_json/utils.py)\n- [todo_logic.py](../../workspace/todo_cli_json/todo_logic.py)\n\n## Checklist\n- [x] Implement CLI parsing and CRUD operations\n- [x] Handle missing/initial JSON\n- [x] Follow CLI interface and data spec\n- [x] Commit code to repo\n- [x] Implement models.py\n- [x] Implement utils.py\n- [x] Implement todo_logic.py (business logic)\n- [x] Implement todo.py (CLI interface)\n\n## Review Status\nAll planned modules are implemented, including the CLI interface (todo.py), following the architecture. Backend and CLI interact correctly, and JSON persistence is in place. Ready for QA to verify functions via manual or automated test cases."}, {"role": "user", "name": "ProjectManager", "content": "Successfully wrote to data/project_board/todo_cli_json/implement_cli_app.md"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Architect", "content": "The implementation follows the architectural plan precisely: all key modules (models.py, utils.py, todo_logic.py, and todo.py) are defined and interact as designed, ensuring maintainability and clear separation of concerns. The README offers fully detailed usage, and the QA review confirms the flow from design to implementation and readiness for testing. The project is now in a stable state for QA.\n\nARCHITECTURE COMPLETE"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-DJwd1icyYIrmiLMqTiamh325MktUT", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": null, "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_FKihREm44k8nOt50GtOyJVsn", "function": {"arguments": "{\"files\":[\"todo_cli_json/models.py\",\"todo_cli_json/utils.py\",\"todo_cli_json/todo_logic.py\",\"todo_cli_json/todo.py\",\"todo_cli_json/README.md\"]}", "name": "git_add"}, "type": "function"}]}}], "created": 1773645971, "model": "gpt-4.1-2025-04-14", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "default", "system_fingerprint": "fp_f7a7a25dd3", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 47, "prompt_tokens": 7933, "total_tokens": 7980, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 5888}}}, "prompt_tokens": 7933, "completion_tokens": 47, "agent_id": "Engineer_eb26f318-3432-47b4-9380-ff7a11d5fd63/eb26f318-3432-47b4-9380-ff7a11d5fd63"}
